Task and Responsibilities:

- Excecute and control of Accounting work;
- Realize a correct, complete and timely administration;
- Excecute improvement processes to realize efficiency in work- and informationprocesses;
- Daily lead and coaching of the Accounting team;
- Ensure daily processing of purchase, sales and bank transactions;
- Set up and control intercompany recharges and reconcilliation;
- Set u and maintain Fixed Assets ledgers;
- Excecute several VAT and CBS returns;
- Work with the treasury department for Cash Management;
- Responsible for accurate financial reporting on a monthly basis; 
- Demurrage Administration;
- Maintain and improve financial processes within the used systems (o.a. Navision and Blue10);
- Representative of the Accounting Department in project groups.

Tasks and Responsibilities:

•	Take care of a flawless, reliable administration of the division Industrial Components;
•	Make sure that the Business Controllers and Group controller have the right information and 
         numbers for monthly reports and prognoses;
•	Professionalization of the department (way of work, financial processes) among other things 
         through automation;
•	Full responsibility for the General Ledger, Debtors- and Creditor administration; 
•	Independent, proactive, socially involved, thrive well within a dynamic production environment 
         and unburden the controllers;
*      Responsible for VAT, ICP and Intrastat returns;
*      Manage team including evaluating individual performances and training of junior employee;
*      Cashflow management including monthly forecasting;
*      Assist Financial and Business Controllers with Budget process; 
*      Collaboration with KPMG for Interim and Final audit;
*      Implement and optimize Digital Purchase Invoices System within Navision ERP System, including    
        training of end users;
*     Being a drive of process iMprovements across the department.

Responsible for primary Dutch legal entity.

Tasks, responsibilities and achievements:

- Full responsibility for the balance sheet and income statement accounts;
- Responsible for month-end, quarter and annual activities, journal entries, accrual accounting, account           reconciliation, intercompany allocations, fee allocation, reporting etc;
- Reviewing and analyzing the entities results (a.o. several fee flows, balance sheet and income statement fluctuations);
- External and internal audit support, communication with auditors;
- Calculating taxes, ensuring tax compliance;
- Preparing and assist in creating the local GAAP financial statements;
- Ensuring compliance with internal and external requirements (Sarbanes-Oxley, local GAAP);
- Identifying and driving process improvements caused by organizational changes, acquisitions/take overs or changes due to law and regulations;
- optimizing the use of the system (Unit 4 Business World).

Tasks, responsibilities and achievements:

- Provide training and assist new and existing employees in SAP and internal processes;
- Performing system tests to ensure that system upgrades, implementations and carve outs went according to plan;
- Assist in the implementation of new businesses as well as carve outs of existing businesses;
- First Contact person for Accounting department when having SAP issues.

Responsible for two large manufacturing Dutch legal entities.

Tasks, responsibilities and achievements:

- Full responsibility for the balance sheet and income statement accounts;
- Responsible for month-end activities, journal entries, accrual accounting, account reconciliation, intercompany allocations etc;
- Reviewing and analyzing the entities results (cost analysis, operating income, gross profit, balance sheet and income statement fluctuations);
- External and internal audit support, communication with auditors;
- Calculating taxes, ensuring tax compliance;
- Preparing and assist in creating the local GAAP financial statements, converting it from US Gaap;
- Ensuring compliance with internal and external requirements (Sarbanes-Oxley, US GAAP, local GAAP);
- Identifying and driving process improvements;
- Controlling the quality of the output from other departments in SAP, advising correct accounting practice;
- Improving the relationship and communication between Finance and the divisions;
- Participation in several Accounting and other projects (f.e. werkkostenregeling);
- Power User of SAP system, carve out of sold division and implementation of new division into SAP existing legal entities, training of new employees on use of SAP in domestic and foreign countries;
- As of May 2014 secretary of Works Council (OR).
